sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Client (Holder)
    participant LS as Lock Service
    participant ZK as ZK Quorum
    participant R as Redis Node(s)
    participant Res as Protected Resource

    Note over C,Res: acquire(key) -> work -> release, with fencing token
    C->>LS: acquire(key, ttl)
    alt ZooKeeper / etcd path
        LS->>ZK: create ephemeral sequential /locks/{key}/lock-N
        ZK-->>LS: znode + seq
        alt my seq is lowest
            ZK-->>LS: lock granted
            LS-->>C: token = monotonic_seq
        else not lowest
            LS->>ZK: watch znode just-before-mine
            Note over LS,ZK: wait for predecessor delete
            ZK-)LS: predecessor released
            LS-->>C: token = monotonic_seq
        end
    else Redis SETNX path
        LS->>R: SET key owner_id NX EX ttl
        alt OK
            R-->>LS: acquired
            LS-->>C: token (best-effort, not monotonic under failover)
        else nil (held)
            R-->>LS: nil
            LS-X C: not acquired (retry with backoff)
        end
    end

    Note over C,Res: critical section -> writes carry fencing token
    C->>Res: write(payload, token)
    Res->>Res: check token >= last_seen_token
    alt token valid
        Res-->>C: write OK; last_seen_token = token
    else token stale (GC pause / partition)
        Res-X C: REJECTED (fencing guard)
    end

    C->>LS: release(key, owner_id)
    alt ZK path
        LS->>ZK: delete znode (or session ends -> auto-release)
    else Redis path
        LS->>R: Lua: if get(key)==owner_id then del(key)
    end
    LS-->>C: released
    Note over LS: TTL expiry is the safety net for crashed holders
